{
  "text": "Remark 3. In general cases, \u0394 -quasiconcave, \u0394 -quasiconcave-like, and usual quasiconcave functions are independent of each other. See examples in [CITATION_1] . Let : R \u2192 R, = \u2212R + . Then the partial order on R is \"\u2264\" (less than or equal to);, hence, the \u0394 -quasiconcave, \u0394 -quasiconcavelike, and usual quasiconcave property of coincide (the usual quasiconcave function means that for any 1 , 2 , \u2208 R,",
